A rampaging fire on Monday engulfed a storey building formerly housing staff of the Nigerian Railway Corporation in Offa, Offa local government area of Kwara State. The fire, which happened close to midnight of the day, was allegedly caused by an undergrowth fire ignited by an unknown person. The fire subsequently spread to the affected storey building. It was also gathered that the fire razed down six out of the 12 rooms in the building. The spokesperson of the Kwara State Fire Service Hassan Adekunle confirmed the incident to our correspondent.   BREAKING: Lagos begins rebuilding Igbosere, Nigeria’s…     Fayemi mourns Adeyemi     OPEC approves 1,718,000b/d for Nigeria   - Advertisement - Adekunle said that “fire officer called SFS Soliu was the one who quickly summoned the service to the scene at Olagunju House, GRA in Offa town around 11 pm. He said: “It was an undergrowth fire which later spread to an abandoned storey building formerly used as railway quarters in Offa local government area, Offa, Kwara state. “Out of the 12 rooms in the storey building, six rooms were affected by the ravaging inferno before it was totally eliminated by the firemen.” He urged the “general public to always play safe especially in this harmattan period.”